# Public page persona and visual contracts

## Rule

Public-facing pages are product contracts. Copy, visuals, analytics, routing, and
CTA behavior must describe and trigger real functionality.

## Checklist

1. Public analytics must not require authenticated clients unless the page itself
   requires auth.
2. Persona or segment detection must have explicit defaults and privacy-safe data
   collection.
3. CTAs must route to existing pages and preserve expected query params.
4. Sample/demo links must load real samples or clearly labeled placeholders.
5. Visual claims must match product capability; do not imply unsupported features.
6. Design tokens should be centralized; avoid one-off colors, spacing, and fonts
   scattered across components.
7. Accessibility basics apply: semantic headings, keyboard flow, focus states,
   reduced motion, alt text, contrast, and responsive layouts.

## Pre-commit check

- [ ] Public CTAs resolve.
- [ ] Authenticated and anonymous paths are both safe.
- [ ] Copy-code parity was checked.
- [ ] Visual changes use shared tokens where the repo has them.
